&lt;p&gt;The Associate Advisor Guide will be responsible for making daily outbound sales calls, taking inbound inquires, and conducting sales activities directly with prospects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Functions for the Associate Advisor Guide will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Associate Advisor Guide will identify, qualify, and develop quality sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle lead generation programs, call campaigns and strategies to acquire new clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage clients through inbound calls and follow-up outbound calls, e mail and other approved media.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhibit a high degree of energy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage prospective clients by building trusting relationships with a high degree of integrity and personal accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure exceptional service and satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in an open-communication environment within a busy team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties or tasks as assigned by management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree from an accredited institution preferred (preferably Business, Economics, Accounting or Finance related).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial services industry experience preferred; inside sales, relationship management, or client service experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekend availability preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills (verbal and written) with the ability to influence and motivate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Salesforce, MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with high-level, busy professionals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be highly flexible and confidential with all matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
