&lt;p&gt;As a key member of the Operations Team, the Billing Specialist partners with advisors, internal teams, and external stakeholders to ensure accurate and timely billing for Mercer Advisors’ investment management clients. This role is responsible for maintaining billing integrity, updating billing instructions, processing fees, resolving discrepancies, and supporting efficient revenue recognition processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform monthly billing audits, including fee calculations, account troubleshooting, and adjustment processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and maintain client accounts and household structures to ensure accurate fee schedule assignments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with advisors and internal stakeholders to update and maintain billing instructions, ensuring alignment with client agreements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile direct debit results and ensure timely and accurate fee collection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to billing-related inquiries from advisors and Client Service teams in a timely and professional manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Trading and Client Service teams to ensure sufficient account liquidity for billing debits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively track, manage, and follow up on outstanding, failed, or rejected fee transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate root causes of failed collections and coordinate resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with advisors, Client Service, and Trading teams to facilitate collections, including funding accounts, re-processing fees, or updating client billing setups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed records of collection efforts and outstanding balances; provide regular reporting on aged receivables and collection status&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify trends in collection issues and recommend process improvements to reduce failed or delayed billing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
